Introduction
2148 010 442 0505, or as commonly known by the Revolutionists as “Chilli”. Chilli is Bean's partner in crime in the story Fractured by Time. Chili serves as Bean’s assistant for the Revolutionists. When not assisting Bean at the Revolutionists, Chilli is working hard as a Journalist for the Chicago Tribune.

Born on May 5, 2148 in Chicago to a middle class family. Chilli faced a few struggles growing up, but never any true problems as being part of the middle class granted her more freedom compared to the lower class. From a young age Chilli always thrived to become a renowned journalist. At the age of 16 Chilli landed an internship at the Chicago Tribune, in which she was assigned to write a report about the Revolutionist rally. It was at the rally where Chilli met Bean for the first time.

At the age of 18 Chilli lands her first job as a journalist for the Chicago Tribune, additionally she joins the Revolutionists when she finds out that Bean has joined the Revolutionists. Additionally, it was around this time when she is given the name Chilli due to her being close to Bean. Together Chilli and Bean work on the missions assigned to them by the Revolutionists. After 4 years Chilli becomes Bean’s assistant in the Revolutionists after he is appointed their leader.

Appearance
The name “Chilli” was given to her due to her close connection with Bean. Although her name was given due to her relation with Bean, it sure does match her personality. Chilli’s blonde hair creates a popping impression to anyone that meets her, given that she typically wears black colored clothing.

Personality
There's more than meets the eye in the case of Chilli, but two things you'll never forget are that she's cheerful and playful. Of course she's also considerate, relaxed and balanced, but in smaller doses and they're often spoiled by habits of being venomous as well. Her cheerfulness though, is what she's most well-liked for. On many occasions people will count on this and his sentimentality especially when they need comforting or support. Nobody's perfect of course and Chilli has plenty of less favorable traits too. Her childish nature and insincerity aren't exactly fun to deal with, much to the annoyance of Bean. Fortunately her playfulness helps keep them in check for at least a little.
